Peru Stocks: Volcan, Rio Alto Gain; Intergroup, Alicorp Decline

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y   a n d   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 
2011-07-15T21:54:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/peru-stocks-volcan-rio-alto-gain-intergroup-alicorp-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 5:42 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 0.8 percent to 20,345.75. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1.2 percent to 2,606.41.  Peruvian mining companies advanced as gold closed at a
record and copper prices rose.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, rose 3 percent to a six-week high of 3.09 soles. Cia.
de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner, rose 1.9 percent to $40.01.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1) 
(MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, advanced
2.9 percent to a one-month high of 3.50 soles.  Rio Alto Mining
Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration company, climbed 1.7
percent to $2.34.  Food, utility and financial services companies fell after
Peru’s National Statistics Institute said gross domestic product
rose at the slowest pace in 15 months in May.  Intergroup Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , owner of
Peru’s fourth-largest bank Interbank, fell the most in two
weeks, sliding 1.6 percent to $24.90.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE),
Peru’s largest foodstuff maker, declined 1.7 percent to 5.90
soles. Edegel SA (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peru unit of  Spain ’s Endesa
SA, dropped 1.9 percent to 1.55 soles.  To contact the reporters on this story:
